{{Quote|You are one of a select few chosen to participate in a special hunt, for a ''special'' prey.|[[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]]|<ref name="Star Wars: Bounty Hunter">''[[Star Wars: Bounty Hunter]]''</ref>}}
'''The Hunt''' was the term used for the event in which [[Count of Serenno/Legends|Count]] [[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]] hired [[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett]] and [[Montross (bounty hunter)|Montross]] to hunt down and destroy the [[Bando Gora/Legends|Bando Gora]] leader, [[Komari Vosa]] in [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]]. Whoever succeeded was to get a bounty of 5,000,000 [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]]. Other than ridding the galaxy of the [[Bando Gora/Legends|Bando Gora]], the true goal of the hunt was to find a worthy template for the [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic]] [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone troopers]].

The hunt waged through many worlds, such as [[Oovo IV/Legends|Oovo IV]], [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], and [[Malastare/Legends|Malastare]]. It was at the [[Bogden/Legends|Bogden]] moon of [[Kohlma]] that Jango Fett tracked Vosa's stronghold.

The two engaged in one last battle. The duel waged on into Vosa's throne room, where Jango mortally wounded her. As she grasped for life, Jango hesitated to kill her. Dooku entered the room and finished off his old apprentice, and chose Fett as the template for the [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Clone Army]]. Fett accepted, on the condition that he receive the [[Boba Fett/Legends|first clone]] for himself, unmodified.

